youthful appearance that conceals his age and a combined insatiable
curiousity and lack of fear that will probably prevent him from reaching
any age where perpetual youth would be a benefit. It does beg the question
- do all old kender look young, or are there just no old kender?

away from me.  One dwarf told me that we all look the same so how would he

more horrible thing.  A bunch of kenders are all at the end of an alley
while people throw stones at them. I scream at them to stop until a large
human grabs me and throws me at the other kenders.  I was glad to be with
them, but not under those circumstances.  I did see my sister, Yendiolf.
She was doing fine except for a few cuts on her head.  Suddenly a rock hits
me in the leg.  I get mad and throw the only rock I had which was the ruby.
It was quite large but it missed everyone and rolled past them into the
streets.  The humans ran after it and started to fight each other for it.
We kenders decided that nothing more exciting was going to happen so we left.'
